{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[307]] &amp;ndash; After divorcing his wife [[Minervina]], [[Constantine I (emperor)|Constantine]] marries [[Fausta]], the daughter of the retired [[Roman Emperor]] [[Maximian]].
*[[1146]] &amp;ndash; [[Bernard of Clairvaux]] preaches his famous sermon in a field at [[Vézelay]], urging the necessity of a [[Second Crusade]].  [[Louis VII of France|Louis VII]] is present, and joins the Crusade.
*[[1492]] &amp;ndash; [[Isabella I of Castile|Queen Isabella]] of Castille issues the [[Alhambra decree]], ordering her 150,000 Jewish subjects to convert to [[Christianity]]  or face expulsion.
*[[1717]] &amp;ndash; A [[Sermon (oration)|sermon]] on &quot;The Nature of the Kingdom of Christ&quot; by [[Benjamin Hoadly]], the [[Bishop of Bangor]], provokes the [[Bangorian Controversy]].
*[[1774]] &amp;ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: The [[Kingdom of Great Britain]] orders the port of [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]] closed pursuant to the [[Boston Port Act]].
*[[1822]] &amp;ndash; [[Chios massacre|The massacre of the population]] of the [[Greece|Greek]] island of [[Chios]]  by soldiers of the [[Ottoman Empire]] following an attempted rebellion, depicted by the French artist [[Eugène Delacroix]].
*[[1854]] &amp;ndash; [[Commodore (USN)|Commodore]] [[Matthew Perry (naval officer)|Matthew Perry]] signs the [[Treaty of Kanagawa]] with the [[Government of Japan|Japanese government]], opening the ports of [[Shimoda, Shizuoka|Shimoda]] and [[Hakodate]] to [[United States|American]] trade.
*[[1866]] &amp;ndash; The [[Spanish Navy]] bombs the harbor of [[Valparaíso, Chile]].
*[[1877]] &amp;ndash; The family with [[samurai]] antecedents that responded to the [[Saigō Takamori|Saigō]] army in [[Ōita Prefecture|Ōita]] Nakatsu, rebels.
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; The [[United Kingdom]] establishes a [[protectorate]] over [[Bechuanaland]].
*[[1889]] &amp;ndash; The [[Eiffel Tower]] is officially opened.
*[[1903]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard Pearse]] allegedly makes a powered flight in an early aircraft.
*[[1906]] &amp;ndash; The Intercollegiate Athletic Association of the United States (later the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]]) is established to set rules for college [[sport]]s in the United States.
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; [[Serbia]] accepts [[Austria]]n control over [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; Construction of the ill fated [[RMS Titanic]] begins.
*[[1910]] &amp;ndash; Six North Staffordshire Pottery towns federate to form modern [[Stoke-on-Trent]].
*[[1917]] &amp;ndash; The United States takes possession of the [[Danish West Indies]] after paying $25 million to [[Denmark]], and renames the territory the [[United States Virgin Islands]].
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[March Days|Massacre of ethnic Azerbaijanis]] is committed by allied armed groups of [[Armenian Revolutionary Federation]] and [[Bolsheviks]]. Nearly 12,000 Azerbaijani Muslims are killed.
*  1918   &amp;ndash; [[Daylight saving time]] goes into effect in the United States for the first time.
*[[1921]] &amp;ndash; The [[Royal Australian Air Force]] is formed.
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; The [[Hays Code|Motion Pictures Production Code]] is instituted, imposing strict guidelines on the treatment of [[sex]], [[crime]], [[religion]] and [[violence]] in [[film]], in the U.S., for the next thirty eight years.
*[[1931]] &amp;ndash; An [[1931 Nicaragua earthquake|earthquake]] destroys [[Managua, Nicaragua]], killing 2,000.
*  1931   &amp;ndash; [[TWA Flight 599]] crashes near [[Bazaar, Kansas]] killing 8 including [[Knute Rockne]], head football coach at the [[University of Notre Dame]]
*[[1933]] &amp;ndash; The [[Civilian Conservation Corps]] is established with the mission of relieving rampant unemployment in the United States.
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: Japanese forces [[Battle of Christmas Island|invade]] [[Christmas Island]], then a British possession.
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; World War II: a defecting German pilot delivers a [[Messerschmitt]] [[Messerschmitt Me 262|Me 262A-1]], the world's first operational [[Turbojet|jet-powered]] [[fighter aircraft]], to the Americans, the first to fall into Allied hands.
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; The [[Dominion of Newfoundland]] joins the [[Canadian Confederation]] and becomes the 10th [[Provinces of Canada|Province]] of [[Canada]].
*[[1951]] &amp;ndash; [[Remington Rand]] delivers the first [[UNIVAC I]] computer to the [[United States Census Bureau]].
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; Elections to the [[Territorial Assembly Election in Upper Volta 1957|Territorial Assembly]] of the [[France|French]] colony [[French Upper Volta|Upper Volta]] are held. After the elections [[Unified Democratic Party|PDU]] and [[Voltaic Democratic Movement|MDV]] form a government.
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; In the [[Canadian federal election, 1958|Canadian federal election]], the [[Progressive Conservative Party of Canada|Progressive Conservatives]], led by [[John Diefenbaker]], win the largest percentage of seats in Canadian history, with 208 seats of 265.
*[[1959]] &amp;ndash; The 14th [[Dalai Lama]], [[14th Dalai Lama|Tenzin Gyatso]], crosses the border into [[India]] and is granted [[political asylum]].
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; A [[1964 Brazilian coup d'état|coup d'état in Brazil]] establishes a [[Brazilian military government|military government]], under the aegis of general [[Humberto de Alencar Castello Branco|Castello Branco]].
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; An [[Iberia Airlines]] [[Convair 440]] crashes into the sea on approach to [[Tangier]], killing 47 of 51 occupants.
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; The [[Soviet Union]] launches [[Luna 10]] which later becomes the first [[space probe]] to enter orbit around the [[Moon]].
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Explorer 1]] re-enters the [[Earth]]'s atmosphere after 12 years in orbit.
*  1970   &amp;ndash; Nine [[terrorism|terrorists]] from the [[Japanese Red Army]] [[Aircraft hijacking|hijack]] [[Japan Airlines Flight 351]] at [[Tokyo International Airport]], wielding [[Katana|samurai swords]] and carrying a [[bomb]].
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; The last [[Armed Forces of the United Kingdom|British]] soldier leaves the [[Malta|Maltese Islands]]. Malta declares its Freedom Day (Jum il-Helsien).
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; The [[Chicago, Rock Island and Pacific]] railroad operates its final train after being ordered to liquidate its assets because of bankruptcy and debts owed to creditors.
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; The first [[WrestleMania]], the biggest wrestling event from the WWE (then the WWF), takes place in [[Madison Square Garden]] in New York.
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; A [[Mexicana de Aviación|Mexicana]] [[Boeing 727]] en route to [[Puerto Vallarta]] erupts in flames and crashes in the mountains northwest of [[Mexico City]], killing 166.
*  1986   &amp;ndash; Six [[metropolitan county]] councils are abolished in [[England]].
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Poll Tax Riots|200,000 protestors take to the streets]] of [[London]] to protest against the newly introduced [[Poll Tax]].
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Georgian independence referendum, 1991]]: nearly 99 percent of the voters support the country's independence from the Soviet Union.
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; The {{USS|Missouri|BB-63|6}}, the last active [[United States Navy]] [[battleship]], is decommissioned in [[Long Beach, California]].
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; The [[Scientific journal|journal]] ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'' reports the finding in [[Ethiopia]] of the first complete ''[[Australopithecus afarensis]]'' skull.
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; [[TAROM Flight 371]] crashed, killing all of the 10 crew and 50 passengers on board.
*  1995   &amp;ndash; [[Selena]], an American singer, was [[Murder of Selena|murdered]] by her friend and employee of her [[Selena Etc.|boutiques]] [[Yolanda Saldívar]] who was embezzling money from the establishments. The event was named &quot;Black Friday&quot; by Hispanics.
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley orders the midnight destruction of Meigs Field Airport
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Iraq War in Anbar Province]] - In [[Fallujah, Iraq]], 4 American [[private military contractor]]s working for [[Blackwater USA]], are killed after being [[31 March 2004 Fallujah ambush|ambushed]].

